- Successful launch of FPS, connecting various banks and stored value facilities (“e-wallets”) seamlessly;
- Release of the Open Application Programming Interface (API) framework for banks and promotion of industry adoption;
- Enhancement of fintech research and talent training;
- Strengthening cross-border fintech cooperation;
- Revision of the “Guidelines on Virtual Banks” and processing virtual bank license applications;
- Smooth operation of the upgraded Fintech Supervisory Sandbox (FSS 2.0);
- Expansion of “Banking with Ease” to promote adoption of RegTech.

Management of the Exchange Fund involves setting investment objectives and portfolio structure. The Exchange Fund Advisory Committee establishes the following investment goals:
(a) Capital preservation;
(b) Ensuring the overall monetary base is fully supported at all times by highly liquid US dollar assets;
(c) Maintaining sufficient liquidity to sustain monetary and financial stability; and
(d) Achieving investment returns within the framework of (a) to (c) to safeguard the long-term purchasing power of the Fund.

